{
    "type": "fix",
    "subject": "Handle null task when creating property task",
    "body": "This commit fixes an issue where a null task is returned when creating a property task. It adds a task definition for the 'property' task type if the task is null, ensuring that the task is properly created. This change prevents a potential NullPointerException and ensures that the property task is initialized correctly."
}

{
    "type": "fix",
    "subject": "Update processBundle call to use correct flag",
    "body": "In the loadResourceMaps method, the last call to processBundle was incorrectly using a flag of false. This commit updates the flag to true, ensuring that the bundle is processed correctly. This change affects the post-condition of the method, depending on how the processBundle method behaves differently when called with true instead of false."
}

{
    "type": "refactor",
    "subject": "Change finalize method to protected",
    "body": "This commit changes the finalize method from public to protected and adds a call to super.finalize() to ensure proper resource release. The finalize method is used to close the resource when the object is garbage collected. This change improves the internal structure of the CBZip2OutputStream class, making it easier to understand and maintain."
}

{
    "type": "style",
    "subject": "Add missing import statement",
    "body": "Added the necessary import statement for ByteArrayInputStream in TarRoundTripTest.java to ensure proper functionality."
}

{
    "type": "fix",
    "subject": "Correctly handle symbolic links in FTP directory scanning",
    "body": "When isFollowSymlinks() is false, the scandir method was incorrectly adding symbolic links to dirsExcluded instead of filesExcluded. This commit fixes this issue by updating the method to add symbolic links to the correct list. This change ensures that symbolic links are properly excluded during FTP directory scanning."
}

{
    "type": "style",
    "subject": "Update comment to use English language",
    "body": "This commit updates the comment above the class declaration in StyleTest.java to use English language instead of German. The change is a minor formatting adjustment to improve code readability."
}

{
    "type": "refactor",
    "subject": "Simplify execSQL method to process only the first result set or update count",
    "body": "This commit refactors the execSQL method to only process the first result set or update count, removing the iteration through multiple result sets or update counts. The method's design rationale has changed to focus on handling a single result set or update count, and its usage remains the same but with the expectation of only seeing the first result set or update count in the output. This change simplifies the method's implementation and reduces its complexity."
}

{
    "type": "fix",
    "subject": "Handle null values in beans when declaring",
    "body": "This commit fixes an issue where null values in beans were not handled properly when declaring them. Now, when a null value is encountered, the bean is undeclared before declaring a new value. This change provides more robustness to the ScriptRunner's executeScript method, ensuring that null values do not cause unexpected behavior. The method's functionality remains the same, but it now handles null values more elegantly."
}

{
    "type": "fix",
    "subject": "Update log level in targetStarted method",
    "body": "Changed the log level from Project.MSG_DEBUG to Project.MSG_VERBOSE in the targetStarted method of CommonsLoggingListener. This change makes the log message more visible to the user, as verbose messages are typically displayed by default, whereas debug messages might be hidden unless explicitly enabled. This update provides more relevant feedback on the build process."
}

{
    "type": "style",
    "subject": "Refactor EchoXML.java comments",
